##Perplexed Venture Capital Li Zhujie: short-term dividends can not change the life and death of an enterprise

Micro-signal, Rancaijing

A feature presentation, a daily in depth report, redefines the innovation economy.

Original by ran CAIJING

By Yan Lijiao

Editor | Zhou Changfan

Under the epidemic situation, fresh electronic commerce ushered in the TUYERE. Order surge, pull new significant, gross profit increase, often in replenishment status. Part of the long-term losses of fresh enterprises, but also take advantage of this opportunity to turn a loss into profit.

Fresh e-commerce has long been seen as the last trillion-dollar market that has not been breached online. Below the speed of life and death, many entrepreneurs want to seize as much as possible the window period of fresh race track. For example, the original focus on b-side customers of the United States network, during the outbreak also opened an additional individual users of the distribution service.

But as we all know, fresh e-commerce is not easy to do. There were about 4,000 entrants in the domestic fresh e-commerce sector, with only 4 percent of them reporting flat revenues, 88 percent reporting losses and only 1 percent making a profit. And this short-term positive can not determine the long-term pattern.

What new changes will the short-term benefits of the epidemic bring to the industry? Can it reshape the pattern of fresh e-commerce industry? After a wave of online user education, when the epidemic is over, how will the fresh e-commerce enterprises such as Youxian, Dingdong shopping, Hema Xiansheng ensure the retention rate and repurchase rate?

"short-term stimulus does not change the life and death of a business. For the right business model is the icing on the cake, for the wrong model is only a temporary shot in the arm. If the model itself is wrong, even if the short-term impact of external forces, the company should die or die. He argues that entrepreneurs in the field of fresh produce can not simply emphasize rhythm. It's more important for entrepreneurs to build on their single store strengths and improve their supply chain capabilities before the model can be validated.

On February 18th, the online business innovation economic warfare project launched its third salon, titled "through the epidemic, how fresh e-commerce can seize new opportunities? " Perplexed venture founding partner Li Zhujie, daily fresh partner and CFO Wang Jun around the topic of fresh e-commerce, in the financial community to share.

Li Zhujie mentioned that there are three main modes in the fresh food industry at present. The first is the store-to-store mode, which belongs to the traditional channel chain. Such enterprises have achieved break-even and even made profits through their long-term development. Some head-end enterprises are already preparing for IPOS, this type of enterprises in some areas have a very high occupancy rate; second, since, this type of enterprises have no pre-warehouse; third, e-commerce delivery mode.

"whether it's a pure online delivery model or an ATM, whether it can be retained and repurchased after the outbreak, and whether it can maintain the current business model is what investors are most concerned about, " Li said, stressing that fresh food is, after all, a daily expense, it's not about impulse spending. When the epidemic is over, and the prices are back to normal, which company will be the long-term winner if it can maintain its current momentum.

Here is the dialogue between CNNMONEY and Li Zhujie:

The supply chain is a fresh enterprise

It's a long-term skill

Fuel Finance and Economics: New consumption is not confused venture focus on one of the track, the epidemic to your investment in the new consumer project what impact? What advice and assistance have you provided to these projects?

Li Zhujie: Online business form of the company is beneficial. We have launched a hotpot food platform, and the revenue is growing very fast. During the outbreak, they also online fresh, in fact fresh is not the original main business. But because the epidemic period, between the factory, the warehouse material flow is interrupted, increases the fresh product category to be the expedient measure.

The main piece of advice we were given at the time was: make sure logistics doesn't become a bottleneck. This can be timely replenishment, sell more goods, can earn more money, thus reducing the investment recovery time. At this point, supply chain advice is definitely too late, because the supply chain itself is to build the long-term basic skills. Enterprises must pay long-term attention to the uniqueness of supply chain.

Burning Finance and Economics: If you look at a fresh e-commerce project at this time, from the investor's point of view, what data dimensions do you pay more attention to?

Li Zhujie: the first is the user repurchase rate; the second is the regional penetration rate. Because the higher the penetration rate, the lower the cost of performance, the more likely the company is to make money; and the third is the ability of a company to transform its supply chain. If it can reinvent the supply chain, its core competitiveness must be higher than other enterprises.

Burning Finance and Economics: After this "epidemic" , you in the fresh e-commerce storage, logistics and distribution model, what inspired?

Li Zhujie: I observed a variety of patterns, many are required to do together online and offline. So I came to the conclusion that whether self-mention or to-shop mode or online ordering, offline delivery mode, enterprises should fight combination. There are limits to any single model. Most importantly, increase the penetration rate, otherwise the cost of performance will not come down and will never be profitable.

Burning Finance and Economics: Some people think that the more fresh e-commerce business sells, the more it loses. From the point of view of investors, do you think this statement is consistent with the facts?

Li Zhujie: The essence of consumer Internet business is to need to drain, fresh more like a drain. It is high frequency, demand is rigid enough, although the customer unit price is low enough, but some fresh enterprise Mori is also very high, in short, there are two sides. So this category is losing money, and if the other categories equalize profits, the company's business model is likely to be flat.

Yonghui supermarket is the essence of fresh drain, and then through the two landlord model to make money, which is a very good business model, Yonghui is also a 100 billion yuan market value of companies. So the fundamental question is not how much fresh losses, but how the entire company's business model is designed and polished.

Burn Finance and Economics: Since last year, the profit pattern of fresh e-commerce has been questioned more, do you think now this problem has been thoroughly resolved? What's next for the industry to take off?

Li Zhujie: It is not too early to make a conclusion. Suppose that a lot of offline business forms are gradually removed, leaving only the city of e-commerce enterprises. They can also make money by raising prices, or by finding a two-landlord model like Yonghui supermarket. But the results should also be observed, during the epidemic, c demand blowout, is a short-term dividend. Wait until after epidemic abate, the price returns to sensitive range, does consumer have to retain after all? How much is left? And what about the business model? That's when you can make some judgments.

Burning Finance and Economics: What is the focus of competition among fresh e-commerce platforms at the current stage? Which platforms do you like best? Do you think there's any chance of a startup entering the fray?

Li Zhujie: At present the focus of competition between fresh platform is running horse enclosure, we are competing for customers and new. But any e-commerce platform, the final essence of competition is to retain and buy back, otherwise grab more territory in fact useless. We are relatively optimistic about the regional king and supply chain King of the enterprise. Regional dominance can achieve very high penetration rates in order to reduce the cost of performance. Have a unique supply chain, in order to provide customers beyond the expectations of the product.

The outbreak will only speed things up

The megatrends aren't GonNa Change

Burning Finance and Economics: Some people say that the current outbreak of fresh e-commerce will be a flash in the PAN, do you agree? What do you think will remain to benefit these companies after the epidemic is over?

Li Zhujie: I don't agree with the theory of a flash in the PAN. In essence, the online adoption of fresh produce is an inevitable long term trend, just say when it will become a reality. At the heart of this is the true retention of data by businesses after the outbreak.

The current outbreak of fresh e-commerce is a blowout, but the long-term so that all people are locked in the home cooking, is not sustainable. After the outbreak, demand is bound to fall. But eating at home is still a very big scene, and we've been looking for innovative companies in the eating at home scene, which is a much bigger track.

Burning Finance: What are your challenges as an investor in 2020? How?

Li Zhujie: As an investment institution, the problem is always the four-word problem —— Investing or not. Fundraising will be harder in 2019, when the epidemic, including government directed funding, will begin to tighten. It will be even more difficult for GP. Investing is a good time, but only if you have enough paper money. You can buy some of the more promising companies that will be affected in the short term at a lower price.

From the point of view of institutional managers, it is also challenging. If you invest a lot of money in an early stage company, investors and entrepreneurs need to figure out how to keep the company alive when subsequent financing can not be expected and does not generate cash flow. It is also difficult to withdraw, these links are all related.

The first strategy is to grasp the enterprise cash flow, to prepare for the worst, the most positive efforts. At the same time, focus on the capitalization of the head of the project, and strive to promote their IPO.

Burn Finance and Economics: Everyone is talking about cash flow. What do you think are the characteristics of cash flow in fresh e-commerce platform? How can entrepreneurs maintain healthy cash flow?

Li Zhujie: cash flow is very important to every business. Fresh e-commerce cash flow actually depends on the relationship between the suppliers, that is, the accounting period. The longer the accounting period, the better the cash flow. Especially in the face of surging demand. No matter which industry, you can put this point out to judge the status of an enterprise industry. The higher the industry, the longer the books it can get.

How do you get a longer term? The essence is the c-end sales capacity to improve. When the sales scale effect is very obvious, the enterprise and supply chain negotiation ability will be greatly improved, the cash flow will be good.

Burning Finance and Economics: What role does epidemic situation play in restructuring fresh electronic commerce industry? Is there room for development for small e-commerce enterprises?

Li Zhujie: restructuring is certain, because the demand side of the blowout, led to a consumption habit than throwing money more strong habit formation, which itself is restructuring. The small fresh e-commerce circuit doesn't have to be a national company like Ali or JD.com. Perhaps a fresh produce company with a very high regional density is enough for an IPO.

We're throwing a pot roast, which is an innovation in the big scene of eating at home. It's itself a Costco model for the vertical industry. To get people to eat better food at cheaper prices. This kind of company, because close to the community convenient, eat is just need, so it develops quite well.

Burning Finance and Economics: Will the cold winter of investment pass this year? And what do you think is the best place to invest in 2020?

Li Zhujie: investment in the winter from the current point of view should be more cold. In the first half of this year, investment institutions are basically in charge of their own investment, are basically doing after the vote. For new projects, there is no way to travel and due diligence, so facing a lot of investment difficulties.

My own judgment is that there will be a surge of growth in the wake of the epidemic, and that the big foundations will focus on investing in these companies, and that they will intensify the Matthew effect. And for ordinary entrepreneurs, capital winter, I think the probability will continue.

But from another point of view, the country will definitely introduce a large number of policies to encourage investment, but also for small and medium-sized enterprises to reduce the burden. Policy-led good, so that the fund will have a turn, we also wait and see.

The outbreak has had little impact on the direction of investment. At present, we generally prefer online business, including online office and other business services, most of the project has been the internet industry, has not been particularly affected. The epidemic is an acceleration, not a change in the real trend. So I think the probability is going to continue to be what the investment community was looking at.
